{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6fae10f-2665-44bb-b450-579613db8990","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** to enable crash dumps with NativeAOT, plus a **volume** for dump storage and **`SYS_PTRACE`** capability for `createdump`:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"    # %e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp\n        - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # Required for NativeAOT — no bundled createdump\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE                      # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi                        # Adjust based on your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_CreateDumpPath`** — critical for NativeAOT since `createdump` isn't bundled with the runtime.\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process; without it, dump generation silently fails.\n- **`emptyDir`** — dumps are ephemeral; swap for a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need them to survive pod restarts. You can also add a sidecar to ship dumps to blob storage.\n- **`sizeLimit`** — full dumps can be large; set this to ~2× your container's memory limit.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aecbe589-de25-4d87-bc78-e8caa183dcc1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n\n1. `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` = `1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n2. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n3. `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n\n\n4. `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` — enable diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nI need to verify the exact environment variable names for NativeAOT specifically, since it doesn't use the CoreCLR runtime like traditional .NET apps. For .NET 8+, NativeAOT does support crash dumps through the `createdump` tool, so I should confirm the correct variable names for this scenario. Now I'm working through the specific Kubernetes configuration needed—the container needs environment variables set, a volume for dump output, and the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so createdump can actually attach to processes and generate the dumps.","outputTokens":1239},"id":"fa525c0c-2ddb-486f-a78e-1fc428ae94dd","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:56:31.894Z","parentId":"332d9f3d-3354-4aa7-b5ee-ad127d042cf4"}
